The paper focuses on online adaptation in robotics, specifically using repertoire-based learning. This falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning techniques such as meta-learning and reinforcement learning, which are commonly found in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of planning algorithms, which are commonly found in the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of computer vision for object recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of a damaged robot and obstacle avoidance, which falls under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
